members.description: The management processor is ready after a successful reset.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: The Management processor is ready The management processor has successfully reset and is now available again. User action: None

members.description: The management processor is in the process of being reset.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: The Management processor is currently in reset The management processor is currently in the process of being reset because of a firmware update or some other event. User action: None

members.description: A device has been inserted in bay 1.
There is no server hardware in CZJ9260730, bay 1.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Perform one of the following: Replace the original server hardware in CZJ9260730, bay 1, or edit the server profile and select different server hardware, server hardware type and/or enclosure group.

members.description: The device in bay 1 has been removed.
There is no server hardware in CZJ9260730, bay 5.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Perform one of the following: Replace the original server hardware in CZJ9260730, bay 5, or edit the server profile and select different server hardware, server hardware type and/or enclosure group.

members.description: The device in bay 5 has been removed.
The BIOS/Hardware is in the error state.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Log into the iLO and view the Integrated Management Log (IML) for additional details.

members.description: There is a device missing or improperly seated on the system board. Service Information: Failure Type:generic, Missing or improperly seated device (Mezz 3 to Enclosure).

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Refer to the Integrated Management Log for details. Remove and then reinstall the failed device. Attempt to boot the server. If the error persists, please contact your support representative.
This trap signifies a device missing or improperly seated on the system board.
